TITLE: Creating a Workflow Function with Inngest in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a function in Inngest that processes integration data. It showcases key features including step-based execution with independent retries, adding sleep/delay periods, and running work in parallel with reliable retry mechanisms.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/content/blog/inngest-add-super-powers-to-serverless-functions.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
inngest.createFunction(
  { name: "Import integration data" },
  { event: "app/integration.connected" },
  async ({ event, step }) => {
    // Steps are retried independently
    const list = await step.run("Fetch data", async () =>
      await getList(event.data.id)
    )
    // Sleep, delay, whatever
    await step.sleep("3d")

    // Run work in parallel - *reliably* w/ retries
    await Promise.all(
      list.map(item =>
        step.run("Process item", async () => await doSomething(item))
      )
    )
  }
)
```

