TITLE: Creating a Weekly Digest Cron Job with Inngest in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a weekly digest cron job using Inngest. It sets up a function that runs every Monday at 9am, loads all accounts, and sends a weekly digest email to each account. The function uses steps to manage the workflow and returns the number of emails sent.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/pages/patterns/_patterns/running-code-on-a-schedule.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { inngest } from "./client";

inngest.createFunction(
  { id: "send-weekly-digest" },
  { cron: "0 9 * * MON" },
  async ({ step }) => {
    const accounts = await step.run("load-accounts", async () => {
      return await getAllAccounts();
    });
    // For each account, reliably send a weekly digest.
    for (let account of accounts) {
      await step.run(
        "send-digest",
        async () => await sentWeeklyDigest(account)
      );
    }
    return `Sent ${accounts.length} weekly digest emails`;
  }
);
```

