TITLE: Running Functions at Specific Times in Python
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to schedule a function to run at a specific date/time using Inngest's step.sleep_until() method in Python. It demonstrates sending an immediate email and then scheduling future work for a specific timestamp.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/pages/docs/guides/delayed-functions.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import inngest
from src.inngest.client import inngest_client

inngest_client = inngest.Inngest(
    app_id="my-app",
)

@inngest_client.create_function(
    fn_id="send-signup-email", 
    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event="app/user.created")
)
async def send_signup_email(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step):
    async def send_email():
        await sesclient.send_email(
            to=ctx.event.data["user_email"],
            subject="Welcome to Inngest!",
            message="..."
        )

    await step.run("send-the-user-a-signup-email", send_email)

    await step.sleep_until("wait-for-the-future", "2023-02-01T16:30:00")

    async def future_work():
        # Code here runs in the future automatically
        pass

    await step.run("do-some-work-in-the-future", future_work)
