TITLE: Generating Video Thumbnails with FFmpeg in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This final step generates a thumbnail image for the rendered video using FFmpeg. It extracts a single representative frame, uploads it to S3 storage, updates the video record with the thumbnail URL, and cleans up temporary files afterward.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/content/blog/banger-video-rendering-pipeline.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
await step.run('generate-thumbnail-and-upload-to-s3', async () => {
  const thumbnailFilePath = `${os.tmpdir()}/${videoId}-thumbnail.jpg`

  await execa(`ffmpeg`, [
    '-i',
    videoFileURL, // ffmpeg will grab input from URL
    '-vf',
    'thumbnail=300',
    '-frames:v', // only one frame
    '1',
    thumbnailFilePath
  ])

  const thumbnailFileURL = await uploadFile({
    Key: `thumbnails/${videoId}.jpg`,
    Body: fs.createReadStream(thumbnailFilePath)
  })

  await dbConnect()
  await VideoModel.updateOne(
    { _id: videoId },
    { $set: { thumbnailURL: thumbnailFileURL } }
  )

  await unlink(thumbnailFilePath)
})
```

