TITLE: Invoking a Function by ID Within the Same App in Python
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use invoke_by_id to call another function within the same app. The first function returns a string value, and the second function invokes the first one by its ID and prints the returned value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/pages/docs/reference/python/steps/invoke_by_id.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
@inngest_client.create_function(
    fn_id="fn-1",
    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event="app/fn-1"),
)
async def fn_1(
    ctx: inngest.Context,
    step: inngest.Step,
) -> str:
    return "Hello!"

@inngest_client.create_function(
    fn_id="fn-2",
    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event="app/fn-2"),
)
async def fn_2(
    ctx: inngest.Context,
    step: inngest.Step,
) -> None:
    output = step.invoke_by_id(
        "invoke",
        function_id="fn-1",
    )

