TITLE: Python implementation using union types with type narrowing
DESCRIPTION: A Python implementation using union types and type narrowing with isinstance() checks. This approach is concise, idiomatic, and works well with type checkers, making it the preferred method for implementing errors as values in Python.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/content/blog/python-errors-as-values.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
# Define a function that returns a union of a User and an error
def get_user(user_id: str) -> User | Exception:
    rows = users.find(user_id=user_id)
    if len(rows) == 0:
        return Exception("user not found")

    return rows[0]

def rename_user(user_id: str, name: str) -> User | Exception:
    # Consume the function
    user = get_user(user_id)
    if isinstance(user, Exception):
        return user

    user.name = name
    return user
```

