TITLE: Creating PostgreSQL Table with pgvector Extension
DESCRIPTION: SQL schema definition for creating a 'stories' table with vector embeddings support using pgvector. The table stores Hacker News stories with their titles, content, and vector embeddings, and creates an HNSW index for faster similarity searches.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/content/blog/render-hacker-news-ai-agent.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS stories (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  title TEXT,
  content TEXT,
  date DATE,
  comments TEXT,
  interest_id INTEGER REFERENCES interests(id),
  embedding vector(1536)
);

