TITLE: Using step.waitForEvent() to Wait for Events in Inngest Functions (v2)
DESCRIPTION: Examples of using step.waitForEvent() in Inngest v2 to wait for specific events. Unlike v3, the event name is passed as the first parameter rather than as part of the options object, while maintaining similar functionality for matching and conditional logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/pages/docs/reference/functions/step-wait-for-event.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Wait 7 days for an approval and match invoice IDs
const approval = await step.waitForEvent("app/invoice.approved", {
  timeout: "7d",
  match: "data.invoiceId",
});

// Wait 30 days for a user to start a subscription
// on the pro plan
const subscription = await step.waitForEvent("app/subscription.created", {
  timeout: "30d",
  if: "event.data.userId == async.data.userId && async.data.billing_plan == 'pro'",
});
```

