TITLE: Using waitUntil for Background Operations
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use waitUntil to handle non-critical async operations without blocking the response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/website/blob/main/content/blog/vercel-cloudflare-wait-until.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
//  GOOD: The sendMetrics function will execute in the background,
// but not block the response from returning to the user
async function POST(request) {
  const data = await createPost(request.body)
  waitUntil(sendMetrics({ metric: 'posts.created', increment: 1 }))
  return new Response(data)
}
```

